			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Anyone that calls you a newbie for asking a simple question is an idiot themselves and needs to get away from the game for 2 seconds and realize that they aren't better than someone just because they know more.<BR>
<BR>
Ahh, Anyway, now that that's out of my system...<BR>
<BR>
The trivial loot code works basically like how experience does.  When you go into the newbie areas like Qeynos Hills or Field of Bone, and everything is green, you wouldn't get experience either, right?  Well, they thought that it would be a good idea to make creatures that drop loot to *not* drop loot if you couldn't gain xp from them.  Basically, if you're level 25+ you wouldn't be able to go into Blackburrow and kill an Elite Gnoll Guard and get a Spiked Collar, or kill a Derv in Nro and get a Cutthroat Ring, unless you were low enough to get experience from them.<BR>
<BR>
I don't like it, but that's just my opinion.  I'd like to be able to go camp the giant fort when I'm level 50 so I can get some free forest loops.  It's a good concept but really needs refinement.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
